# Spec 017 — Orientation & Clarity

Status: Draft
Owner: <you>
Related: 005 R6 (first-run hint — superseded), 009 R1 (click-to-select),
001 R4 / 010 (budget de-emphasis + basemap), 012 R5 (About panel),
018 (LiveNear rebrand — new components use the brand constant)

## Overview

Three first-impression fixes. New visitors land on a map with no
explanation of what the product is — the one-line hint assumes they already
get it. A selected ZIP can only be dismissed via × or Esc — re-clicking the
same area should toggle it off. And with a budget set, over-budget ZIPs at
0.15 opacity wash into the basemap's light water, so "too expensive" and
"lake" read the same. This spec adds a proper welcome modal, click-to-
deselect, and a hatch pattern that makes over-budget areas unmistakable.

## Requirements

- **R1 — Welcome modal.** First visit shows a branded modal: logo, a 2–3
  sentence purpose statement, three one-line how-tos (set a budget / place
  the work pin & pick a commute / click any ZIP for details), and an
  "Explore the map" CTA. Dismissal is remembered in localStorage; Esc and
  the CTA both close it; it can be reopened from a "How it works" link in
  the About panel. Replaces the 005 R6 one-line hint entirely (component,
  test, CSS, and old storage key all retired).
- **R2 — Click-to-deselect.** Clicking the currently selected ZIP on the
  map deselects it (panel closes, outline clears). Selection from top
  movers, ZIP search, or deep links always selects (never toggles). A
  pinned ZIP stays pinned through deselection.
- **R3 — Over-budget hatching.** When a budget is set, over-budget ZIPs
  render a diagonal hatch (canvas-generated, registered via `map.addImage`
  — no static asset) over the existing dimmed fill, visually distinct from
  water and matching the legend's striped over-budget swatch. No budget →
  no hatch anywhere. ZIPs without a value never hatch.

## Non-functional / Constraints

- No new dependencies; the hatch is an 8×8 generated canvas tile.
- Modal follows the existing About-panel a11y pattern (dialog role, Esc,
  visible close affordance); brand name comes from the shared config
  constant so the 018 rename is a one-line flip.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Fresh profile/incognito → welcome modal appears once; "Explore the
      map" dismisses it; reload → it does not reappear; About → "How it
      works" reopens it; Esc closes it.
- [ ] Click a ZIP → panel opens; click the same ZIP → panel closes and the
      outline clears; × and Esc still work; a pinned ZIP's outline survives
      deselection; top-movers click still always selects.
- [ ] Set a budget in a coastal metro → over-budget ZIPs show a hatched dim
      fill clearly distinguishable from water; clear the budget → hatch
      gone; no-data ZIPs unhatched throughout.
- [ ] `npm run test` green, including new welcome-modal, about-link, and
      over-budget-filter tests; old onboarding test removed.

## Out of Scope (explicit)

- Multi-step tours / coach marks; transit mode; any data changes.
- The LiveNear rename itself (spec 018).

